  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Institutional Support for Caritas Diocese of Malakal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is raised to approve &#xA3;9,999.00 for refurbishment of Palica offices in Malakal.   The offices in the mean time will be used by the South Sudan Council of Churches (SSCC) for its peace building programme, AFP (Action for Peace in South Sudan, but in the medium to long term will be handover to the Diocese of Malakal.
Caritas Diocese of Malakal was one of the worse affected dioceses in South Sudan by the conflict that erupted in Juba in December 2013, and quickly spread to greater Upper Nile.  The capture and re-capture of Malakal town by the two worrying parties which happened more than once left the whole infrastructures in the town including Church buildings destroyed.
As a result, the clergy as well as Caritas Diocese of Malakal were left with no choice but to relocate to Juba.  Upto this point in time there is no presence of Caritas Diocese of Malakal in Malakal town.  With situation a bit calming down and with concerted efforts by IGAD and Troika as reflected by the current peace negotiations in Addis Ababa, there are hopes that peace will again return to Malakal.</narrative>
  </description>
